---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Family Documents" description="Placeholder for future protected family-only documents.">
	<section class="panel section prose">
		<p class="eyebrow">Family Documents</p>
		<h2 class="page-title">Protected documents will live here later</h2>
		<p class="page-intro">
			This placeholder is in place for future private PDFs and family-only files. Authentication, Cloudflare Access, and private
			storage are intentionally not added yet.
		</p>
		<div class="grid cards">
			<article class="card">
				<h4>Planned later</h4>
				<p>Protected family resources, permission slips, and forms can be added when the access model is ready.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="card">
				<h4>Current state</h4>
				<p>For now, the page acts as a clear navigation placeholder so the future area is already part of the site structure.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
